You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring-based configuration system randomly freezes and threads are stuck in a `RUNNABLE` state. A thread dump reveals that several threads are blocked inside `java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap.computeIfAbsent`. You locate the following custom hierarchical cache implementation used to resolve dynamic tenant configurations:

java
@Component
public class TenantConfigCache {
    private final Map<String, String> configMap = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    public String getConfig(String tenantId) {
        return configMap.computeIfAbsent(tenantId, id -> {
            if (id.contains(".")) {
                String parentTenant = id.substring(0, id.lastIndexOf("."));
                return getConfig(parentTenant) + "-customized";
            }
            return "default";
        });
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput microservice runs out of memory (`OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`) after a few hours of operation. The application tracks active transactional metadata using a custom cache implemented with `java.util.WeakHashMap`:

java
public class TransactionContextCache {
    private final Map<TransactionId, TransactionMetadata> cache = new WeakHashMap<>();

    public void registerTransaction(TransactionId id, TransactionMetadata metadata) {
        cache.put(id, metadata);
        metadata.setTransactionId(id); 
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where updates to JPA entities are not being saved to the database. The team is using Hibernate as the JPA provider. They implemented a custom collection class `DirtyTrackingList` to audit entity modifications before persisting:

java
@Service
public class InventoryService {
    @Autowired private ProductRepository productRepository;

    @Transactional
    public void processInventory(Long warehouseId) {
        List<Product> products = productRepository.findByWarehouseId(warehouseId);
        List<Product> auditedProducts = new DirtyTrackingList<>(products);

        for (Product product : auditedProducts) {
            product.adjustStock(); // Modifies entity state
        }
        // No explicit repository.save() is called, relying on Hibernate automatic dirty checking
    }
}
